Key Match Events: Denis Undav scored a brace to help Germany win 2-1 at Bosnia-Herzegovina
Hungary held the Netherlands to a 1-1 draw despite being reduced to 10 men
Post-Match Reflections: Following the retirements of Manuel Neuer and Toni Kroos, coach Julian Nagelsmann's team has started a new cycle and their spirited, clean and fluid display bodes well for the future
Miscellaneous Highlights: Germany extended its unbeaten record in the Nations League to three matches
The Netherlands' unbeaten run was almost stopped by Hungary
Others: The match was played at Puskas Arena and Zenica, Bosnia and Herzegovina
